---
// /install — the honest split: what works today (build from source, ~5
// minutes) versus the decided-but-gated distribution future. Every planned
// command renders inside an explicitly PLANNED-labeled block, future tense;
// the install e2e enforces that no install command renders as available
// today and that the old squatted package name never appears.
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import Source from "../components/Source.astro";
import { SITE_NAME, REPO_URL } from "../config";
import { href } from "../lib/url";

const packageName = SITE_NAME.toLowerCase();
const planned = [
  { cmd: `uvx ${packageName}`, note: "run without installing" },
  { cmd: `uv tool install ${packageName}`, note: "the primary documented path" },
  { cmd: `pipx install ${packageName}`, note: "isolated CLI install" },
  { cmd: `pip install ${packageName}`, note: "plain pip, one package" },
];
---

<Base
  title={`Install — ${SITE_NAME}`}
  description="Install from source today (clone, uv, Docker — about five minutes). Package-index distribution is decided but gated; every planned command is future tense until the release gate opens."
  ogImage="/og/og-install.png"
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="kicker">Install</span>
      <h1>One path works today. The rest is future tense.</h1>
      <p class="lead" style="margin-top: 18px; max-width: 64ch;">
        {SITE_NAME} is pre-release: nothing is on any package index. The repository is licensed Apache-2.0
        (ADR-0028). Building from source works now and takes about five minutes; everything else on this page
        is a documented plan behind a human-gated release.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" id="from-source">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-head">
        <span class="kicker">Works today</span>
        <h2>Install from source</h2>
        <p class="lead">
          Prerequisites, honestly: <a href="https://docs.astral.sh/uv/">uv</a>, Docker (for a local,
          digest-pinned Postgres 17 on loopback), and about five minutes.
        </p>
      </div>
      <pre data-analytics-copy-event="install_command_copy" data-analytics-placement="install"><code># pre-release: clone only — no package-index install exists
git clone {REPO_URL}.git && cd {packageName}

uv sync --locked                # toolchain + deps, pinned by uv.lock
uv run irrevon init             # writes irrevon.toml, compose.yaml, .env.example
cp .env.example .env            # local migration bootstrap; no credential
set -a && . ./.env && set +a    # export the generated migration DSN
docker compose up -d --wait     # digest-pinned Postgres 17, loopback only
uv run irrevon init             # now applies the plain-SQL migrations
uv run irrevon doctor           # read-only checks incl. the identity self-test
uv run irrevon demo             # the two-leg flagship story</code></pre>
      <div style="margin-top: 14px;">
        <Source id="quickstart-real" also={["not-published"]} />
      </div>
      <p style="margin-top: 18px;">
        Then step through what the demo recorded: <a href={href("/demo/")}>the One-Way Seat</a>, or follow the{" "}
        <a href={href("/docs/getting-started/")}>getting-started guide</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" id="planned">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-head">
        <span class="kicker">Decided, not yet real</span>
        <h2>Planned distribution — gated</h2>
        <p class="lead">
          The distribution model is decided (one PyPI package, workbench embedded, zero recurring cost) and
          the name is decided — {SITE_NAME}, with PyPI registration of “{packageName}” unblocked pending
          external clearances and the counsel trademark screen. Until the public-release gate opens, none of
          the commands below works, and this site will not pretend otherwise.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="planned-block" data-planned>
        <div class="planned-head">
          <span class="planned-chip">PLANNED — not yet published</span>
          <span class="mono-chip">future tense</span>
        </div>
        <ul class="planned-list">
          {
            planned.map((p) => (
              <li>
                <code>{p.cmd}</code>
                <span>{p.note}</span>
              </li>
            ))
          }
        </ul>
        <p class="planned-note">
          These will work only after: external clearances granted in writing · counsel trademark screen of
          “{SITE_NAME}” · sanitization review · trusted publishing per ADR-0018 · human sign-off. The licensing
          decision is closed — Apache-2.0 (ADR-0028). Publication is never an agent act.
        </p>
        <Source id="install-gated" also={["license-apache2"]} />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" id="uninstall">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-head">
        <span class="kicker">Leaving</span>
        <h2>Uninstall</h2>
        <p class="lead">Nothing global is installed, so removal is complete and local.</p>
      </div>
      <pre><code>docker compose down -v          # drop the local database volume
cd .. && rm -rf {packageName}   # remove the clone (irrevon.toml, .env, compose.yaml live inside it)</code></pre>
      <p class="muted" style="margin-top: 14px; font-size: var(--site-text-small);">
        When packaged distribution exists, uninstall will be documented as package removal plus the same two
        steps — no global state, by design (ADR-0018).
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  .planned-block {
    border: 1px dashed var(--ref-border-strong);
    border-radius: 2px;
    background: var(--ref-layer-panel);
    padding: clamp(20px, 3vw, 32px);
    display: grid;
    gap: 16px;
    max-width: 76ch;
  }
  .planned-head {
    display: flex;
    gap: 10px;
    align-items: center;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }
  .planned-chip {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.6875rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    border: 1px dashed var(--ref-border-strong);
    border-radius: 2px;
    padding: 5px 8px;
    color: var(--ref-ink-2);
  }
  .planned-list {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    display: grid;
    gap: 10px;
  }
  .planned-list li {
    display: flex;
    gap: 16px;
    align-items: baseline;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }
  .planned-list code {
    min-width: 26ch;
  }
  .planned-list span {
    color: var(--ref-ink-3);
    font-size: var(--site-text-small);
  }
  .planned-note {
    color: var(--ref-ink-2);
    font-size: var(--site-text-small);
    max-width: 64ch;
  }
</style>
